      "doctor_failed_response": "Thank you for clarifying that. So to summarize, you have three main issues that began around the same time: **shortness of breath** that has been getting more constant, **irritated, itchy, red eyes**, and a **tender, pink-to-red rash on both shins** that's been present for about a month. You haven't had a cough.\n\nThis constellation of symptoms—affecting your lungs, eyes, and skin—is important. It suggests we need to look for a possible condition that can involve multiple systems of the body. Some possibilities we need to consider include certain inflammatory or autoimmune conditions, infections, or allergic reactions, but we need to investigate further.\n\nTo start, I'd like to perform a physical examination. I'll need to listen to your lungs and heart, take a close look at the rash on your shins, and examine your eyes. Following that, we will likely need to run some tests, which could include blood work and possibly a chest X-ray, to help us understand what's happening.\n\nHow does that plan sound to you? Do you have any questions before we begin the examination?",
